external_knowledge:
- "Musical garden of Japan" refers to the music industry in Japan;
- "Blossomed with collaborations" refers to the number of collaborations on each album;
- "Since the dawn of the new decade" refers to albums released after 2010.

- 'Collaborations' refer to the number of artists involved in creating an album;
- 'Average ratings' are calculated based on user reviews;
- 'Release counts' are the total number of times an album has been released by a label;
- 'Album counts' are the total number of albums each artist has produced.

- "albums like chameleons, able to blend into more than one genre" refers to albums that have more than one genre associated with them;
- "genre versatility" refers to the number of genres an album is associated with;
- "from the most to the least versatile" means ordering the albums by the number of genres in descending order.

- "blossomed with critical acclaim" refers to albums that have received high ratings and a sufficient number of reviews;
- "at least 2 reviews" ensures that the rating is based on a reasonable sample size;
- "average rating of 4 stars or higher" indicates that the album is highly rated by users;
- "how many times have they been played" refers to the total number of plays recorded in the `access_logs` table.

- 'shining stars' refers to albums that have the highest average ratings;
- 'captured the hearts of many listeners' refers to albums with the most reviews;
- 'top 10' means the query returns the top 10 albums based on the ranking criteria.

- "five admirers" refers to at least 5 reviews;
- "shone brightly" refers to an average rating above 4;
- "most frequently visited" refers to the highest number of access events.

- 'Collaborators' include both main and featured artists;
- 'Main Artist' is the primary creator of the album;
- 'Featured Artist' is an additional artist who contributes to specific tracks or the entire album;
- 'Average Rating' is the mean of all ratings given by users;
- 'Number of Reviews' is the total count of reviews for the album;
- 'Number of Genres' is the count of unique genres associated with the album;
- 'Number of Albums by the Main Artist' is the total count of albums the main artist has contributed to.

- "Top-rated" refers to albums with the highest average ratings and the most reviews;
- "Each genre" indicates that the selection is done within the same genre category;
- The top 3 albums are selected based on a combination of the number of reviews and average rating.

- "Labels" are music labels that release albums;
- "Albums" are collections of music tracks;
- "Collaborations" refer to multiple artists working together on an album;
- "Ratings" are user evaluations of the quality of an album, typically on a scale;
- "Releases" are the instances of albums being made available to the public;
- "Gardeners" and "plants" are metaphors for labels and albums, respectively.

- "high rating" refers to an average rating greater than 3;
- " significant number of collaborations" refers to the count of collaborations an artist has;
- The albums are ordered by their titles, reflecting a structured presentation of the results.
